[normal]Written Evidence from [bold]Joseph Whelan, Head of Passenger Transport Services, [bold]Cambridgeshire County Council (TIC 069)[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;[bold]1.[bold]              [bold]Intr[bold]o[bold]duction[bold]&#xa0;[bold]1.1
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Cambridgeshire is a diverse county, consisting of large rural areas, market towns and the city of 
[normal]Cambridge
[normal].
[normal] The issues facing rural areas vary considerably across the county. In Fenland, in the north of the county, the key concerns are linked to an ageing
[normal] population, deprivation, educational attainment and health inequalities, while in rural areas to the south of the county the overriding issue is the availability of transport to access services. Improving transport has an important role to play in reducin
[normal]g social exclusion, improving accessibility and helping people to live independent lives, but the location of services and choices as to how they are provided often have significant transport impacts. 
[normal]Different groups in the county face a variety of transp
[normal]ort problems, for example children and young people often rely on parents to provide transport where public transport opportunities do not exist
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]1.2
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]On 30
[normal]th
[normal] January 
[normal]2012 
[normal]the County Council 
[normal]Cabinet 
[normal]committed to a three year phased programme of 
[normal]removing (in two
[normal] steps) 
[normal]the £2.7 million used to subsidise bus services. 
[normal]In its place it committed £1.5M of targeted investment 
[normal]to 
[normal]be spent 
[normal]providing transport solutions that
[normal] better reflect the needs of
[normal] local areas
[normal].
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]1.3
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]This investment in local transport solution and is part
[normal] of a wider Programme of work being delivered under the Cambridgeshire Future Transport Programme. The CFT Programme
[normal] is focusing on:
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]•
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]strengthen
[normal]ing
[normal] the connections between transport solutions and community outcomes,
[normal]•
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]enabl
[normal]ing 
[normal]the pooling of resources across
[normal] boundaries
[normal] where applicable
[normal]•
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]providing
[normal] a strategic framework to bring partners together
[normal]•
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]stimulat
[normal]ing
[normal] opportunities to create new community joint ventures to operate as local 
[normal]delivery
[normal] bodies
[normal]•
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]engag
[normal]ing 
[normal]more widely with other services to explore the potential to innovate and improve service accessibility in 
[normal]order to 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]provide transport solutions that better meet communities’ needs 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]1.4
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]In 2012 Cambridgeshire
[normal] [bold]Co
[normal]unty 
[normal]C
[normal]ouncil
[normal] [bold]embarked on 
[normal]this ambitious programm
[normal]e to
[normal] increase and improve 
[normal]accessibility
[normal]. A key part of the CFT Programme is a comprehensive review of the transport needs of communities and how the previous bus subsidies are being spent. Value for money and cost (in £) per subsidised bus journey are crit
[normal]ical dimensions of this review. 
[normal]The methodology of this approach, how the 
[normal]needs of different groups/sections of the commun
[normal]ity together with the challenge
[normal]s faced are all described in further detail below. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]1.5
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]For the local transport solutions work, the County
[normal] has been divided up into 13 areas or tranches. The engagement work described below has been undertaken (fully) in Areas A to D and is being launched in 
[normal]October 
[normal]2013 in Area E F and G.  
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]2. [bold]              [bold]Identification of Demand for Passenger Transport in Isolated [bold]Communities[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]2.1
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The 
[normal]key feature of the approach to developing new local transport solutions 
[normal]using input and information gained through engagement
[normal] rather than consultation. Progr
[normal]ess to date has implemented new 
[normal]solutions that have been co-produced with local co
[normal]mmunities. The approach of subsidising bus services on the bas
[normal]is o
[normal]f existing passengers has been replaced
[normal] with 
[normal]encouraging community involvement throughout the process and broadening the reach to include potential passengers, as well as existing
[normal]. The resul
[normal]t has 
[normal]transport 
[normal]that is more (commercially) 
[normal]sustainable and appropriate.  
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]2.2
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Decisions 
[normal]are being 
[normal]made on an area by area basis
[normal] about the 
[normal]level 
[normal]and type 
[normal]of engagement that is most appropriate for that community.  
[normal]Local engagement plans 
[normal]are in place and have 
[normal]been contributed to by 
[normal]local members and the 
[normal]local 
[normal]parish council
[normal]. 
[normal]This local engagement 
[normal]is 
[normal]reflect
[normal]ing 
[normal]the diversity of communities within Cambridgeshire 
[normal]whilst 
[normal]recognisin
[normal]g and responding to differences.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]2.3
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
