[normal]2.11
[normal]              
[normal]Engagement Process
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]The 
[normal]engagement process provid
[normal]es 
[normal]structure whilst enabling flexibility to adapt to the needs to the local area.
[normal] The following 
[normal]outlines 
[normal]the basic process 
[normal]from which 
[normal]different engagement techniques can be 
[normal]employed at a local/community level dep
[normal]ending on the 
[normal]area
[normal].
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]Stage 1[bold] –
[normal]Meet with local District
[normal] and 
[normal]County 
[normal]Council 
[normal]members and Parish 
[normal]C
[normal]ouncils to agree a community engagement plan and to answer questions on the CFT process.
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]Stage 2 [bold]– Begin the 
[normal]q
[normal]uantitative data collection of current travel patterns and bus usage a
[normal]s well as collating any existing transport data within the area.  
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]Stage 3[bold] – Set up initial meetings
[normal] with identified community groups
[normal]. Th
[normal]ese
[normal] meeting
[normal]s
[normal] will have a number of purposes. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]Stage[bold] 4 [bold]–
[normal] [bold]W
[normal]orking groups to put together options
[normal] 
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]Stage 5 [bold]–
[normal] 
[normal]Carry out evidence gathering to fill any gaps in data and knowledge. 
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]Stage[bold] [bold]6[bold] – 
[normal]Feedback options to the parish councils and local communities for comment, amendments
[normal].
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]              [bold]Stage [bold]7 [bold]– 
[normal]Finalise design of solution
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]Stage 8[bold] – Take it back to the wider community for approval – This 
[normal]is 
[normal]via
[normal] members, the parish councils and community events.
